code        operands    stack       comments
====================================================================================================
halt        0           0           halts the virtual machine

cload       1           1           pushes a constant on the stack
vload       1           1           pushes a global on the stack
aload       0           -1          pops an array reference and index, and pushes the array item

vstore      1           -1          pops a value from the stack into a global
astore      0           -3          pops a value into an array slot

drop        0           -1          removes the top-of-stack.
dup         0           +1          duplicates the item on TOS.

amake       1           +1          creates an array and pushes a reference to it
adel        0           -1          deletes an array pointed to by the TOS
cclone      0           +1          creates a copy of a constant pool object on TOS
mclone      0           +1          creates a copy of a dynamic memory object on TOS
cmake       0           0           creates an instance of a constant pool prototype on TOS
mmake       0           0           creates an instance of a dynamic memory prototype on TOS
del         0           -1          frees the memory used by an object on TOS

iowrite     0           -1          writes the top of stack to the IO device
ioread      0           +1          reads a line of text from the IO device onto the stack
iostyle     1           0           sets the IO device style

i2s         0           0           converts the TOS from integer to string
i2f         0           0
f2s         0           0
f2i         0           0

p2s         0           0           converts the TOS from property reference to string

addi        0           -1          adds two integers
subi        0           -1          subtracts an integer from another
muli        0           -1          multiplies two integers
divi        0           -1          divides an integer by another

addf        0           -1          adds two floats
subf        0           -1          subtracts an float from another
mulf        0           -1          multiplies two floats
divf        0           -1          divides an float by another
